	abstract = {We study the educational effect of the Academic Support Center at Kogakuin University. Following the initial assessment, it appeared that bias leads to an underestimation of the Center’s true effect. To address this issue we applied the theory of causal inference, where the treatment effect of face-toface personal assistance (F2F) is defined by the difference between a scenario in which a student uses F2F and a scenario in which the same student does not. To estimate the treatment effect, we make use of T-learner, a machine learning model within the framework of causal inference.},
